#. §0: `Divides a b`
#. §1: `∃ k, b = a * k`
#. §2: `k`
#. §3: `0 = 7 * k`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L03_DividesZero
msgid "# Level 3\n"
"\n"
"Does 7 divide 0?\n"
"\n"
"🤔 **Read the definition, not your instinct.** §0 says §1.\n"
"So we need a §2 with §3."
msgstr ""

#: GameServer.RpcHandlers
msgid "intermediate goal solved! 🎉"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld
msgid "Welcome to **Divisibility World**! We'll build the divisibility relation from the\n"
"ring axioms, then find out which axiom has been holding up the floor all along."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `1 = 0`
#. §1: `w = w * 1 = w * 0 = 0`
#. §2: `have hzero : w = 0 := by rw [← Z.mul_one w, h, Z.mul_zero]`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L04_OneNeZero
msgid "🤔 If §0, then §1. 👉 Try §2"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `1 ≠ 0`
#. §1: `1 = 0`
#. §2: `0 = 1`
#. §3: `False`
#. §4: `intro h`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L04_OneNeZero
msgid "# Level 4\n"
"\n"
"Here is a fact you have used since you were four.\n"
"\n"
"§0\n"
"\n"
"🤔 **But why?** Look at the axioms. Ring axioms, order axioms, Well-Ordering.\n"
"Which one rules out a world where §1?\n"
"\n"
"Consider the ring with a single element, where §2 and nothing else exists.\n"
"Associativity holds. Commutativity holds. Distributivity holds. Trichotomy holds,\n"
"since everything is zero. Well-Ordering holds vacuously.\n"
"\n"
"**Every axiom survives. Except one.**\n"
"\n"
"## Proof by contradiction\n"
"\n"
"We assume the opposite and derive §3. 👉 Try §4"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld
msgid "Divisibility"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "Linearity"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L02_Transitivity
msgid "Level completed! 🎉\n"
"\n"
"The witness was the **product of the witnesses**. Divisibility composes."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `∃ k, b * x + c * y = a * k`
#. §1: `b = a * k`
#. §2: `c = a * l`
#. §3: `b * x + c * y = a * (k * x + l * y)`
#. §4: `exact ⟨k * x + l * y, by rw [hk, hl, Z.mul_add, Z.mul_assoc, Z.mul_assoc]⟩`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "🤔 We want §0, and Lean will not let us postpone naming that k. We must produce it first. Since §1 and §2, we get §3. 👉 Try §4"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `b = a * k`
#. §1: `c = b * l`
#. §2: `exact ⟨k * l, by rw [hl, hk, Z.mul_assoc]⟩`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L02_Transitivity
msgid "🤔 We have §0 and §1. Substitute the first into the second. 👉 Try §2"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "We've proven our first theorem! 🎉\n"
"\n"
"💡 **Pro-tip**\n"
"\n"
"Notice what Lean forced on us. We had to name the witness *before* we could prove anything about it. In Ross we call this **Have/Want**. Here it isn't advice. It's a compiler error."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L04_OneNeZero
msgid "One is not equal to zero"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `obtain ⟨k, hk⟩ := hb`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "👉 Try §0 to unpack the first divisibility."
msgstr ""

#: GameServer.RpcHandlers
msgid "level completed with warnings… 🎭"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `obtain`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L02_Transitivity
msgid "👉 Unpack both hypotheses with §0."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "Rewrites the goal using an equation."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `obtain ⟨k, hk⟩ := h`
#. §1: `h : ∃ k, P k`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "Unpacks an existential. §0 splits §1 into a witness and a proof."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `pos_nonempty`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L04_OneNeZero
msgid "Level completed! 🎉\n"
"\n"
"💡 **Pro-tip**\n"
"\n"
"The axiom that did the work was §0: *some positive integer exists.*\n"
"\n"
"It is the most boring axiom on the list. Nobody ever cites it. And without it,\n"
"every theorem in this game is true of a set with exactly one element.\n"
"\n"
"The axioms you never think about are the ones holding up the floor."
msgstr ""

