msgid "Ross ℤ Game"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L02_Transitivity
msgid "Transitivity"
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L03_DividesZero
msgid "Level completed! 🎉\n"
"\n"
"Every integer divides zero. **Zero included.**\n"
"\n"
"💡 **Pro-tip**\n"
"\n"
"But zero divides only zero. Divisibility is not symmetric."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `rw [hzero] at hw`
#. §1: `exact Z.not_pos_zero hw`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L04_OneNeZero
msgid "Finish it. 👉 §0 then §1"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `hc`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "Now do the same with §0."
msgstr ""

#. §0: `pos_nonempty`
#. §1: `obtain ⟨w, hw⟩ := Z.pos_nonempty`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L04_OneNeZero
msgid "🔍 The axiom §0 says a positive integer exists. 👉 Try §1"
msgstr ""

#. §0: `Divides a b`
#. §1: `∃ k, b = a * k`
#. §2: `obtain`
#. §3: `hb`
#. §4: `hc`
#. §5: `obtain ⟨k, hk⟩ := hb`
#. §6: `hb`
#. §7: `k`
#. §8: `hk : b = a * k`
#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L01_Linearity
msgid "# Level 1\n"
"\n"
"Welcome to Divisibility World! We'll start with the workhorse of the entire game.\n"
"\n"
"## Divisibility\n"
"\n"
"The definition says:\n"
"\n"
"§0 means §1\n"
"\n"
"That existential is the whole story. To **use** a divisibility, we extract its witness. To **prove** one, we supply a witness.\n"
"\n"
"## The §2 tactic\n"
"\n"
"We have two divisibilities, §3 and §4, but each is locked inside an existential. 👉 Specifically, try\n"
"\n"
"§5\n"
"\n"
"This unpacks §6 into a witness §7 and the fact §8."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DivisibilityWorld.L03_DividesZero
msgid "Everything divides zero"
msgstr ""

